definitions.definition: To introduce (something) between other things; especially to insert (possibly spurious ) words into a text.
examples: in verse 74, the second line is clearly interpolated , probably by some unknown medieval scribe
When interpolating an explanatory gloss, please enclose it in square brackets to make clear that it is interpolated .

definitions.definition: To estimate the value of a function between two tabulated points.
During the course of processing some data, and in response to a directive in that data, to fetch data from a different source and process it in-line along with the original data.

main_definition: ( transitive , intransitive ) To introduce (something) between other things; especially to insert (possibly spurious ) words into a text.
secondary_definitions: ( mathematics ) To estimate the value of a function between two tabulated points.
